When we moved to the area we searched for a Good Christain church and 1st tried Calvary Chapel Downey. We were impressed with Pastor Jeff Johnson so much that we decided to stay and we've been there almost 2 years now. He's a Good Man of God and he tells us as Christains how we should be living our lives for the Lord. He's not afraid to tell us like it is and he ALWAYS teaches from the Bible and ALWAYS teaches how to be Saved so that if you aren't Saved, he will tell you how You can be with God some day. We couldn't ask for a better church. We are Very Happy we went to Calvary first. We found a home in Calvary Chapel of Downey. If you haven't been here then PLEASE just try it once. < Review>
Started Calvary Chapel Downey in 1979. Spoke with Pastor Jeff Johnson, told him I was new, loved the depth of his messages, needed class for my developmentally challenged daughter, sadly there was none. So we prayed, 3 mos later I started  "Special Kids Sunday School". I've taught special children & adults for 35yrs!
I highly recommend Calvary Chapel Downey, you LEARN God's word expositionally (verse by verse), they provide CHILDREN's MINISTRIES from infant care, toddlers, pre-school thru high school. Teachers are dedicated, teaching the WORD to children!!
If you're looking for a church that provides any/all these ministries come on OVER!!<//Review>

I just moved to Lake Forest from LA where I am spoiled with amazing mexican marts like El Super, El Superior & North Gate. I found this place on Yelp/Google and the reviews were good. But my experience was horrible. The service was pretty horrible, and the guy are the carnicera purposely ignored me  (although I was thier first with no one else around) as soon as a hispanic gentleman walked up. It was unfortunate. The workers even talked trash about me in spanish and I am 85% fluent in spanish. It was almost like a caucasian female never stepped foot in that market before. The prices were okay, nothing comparable to the markets I am used too. I wouldnt go again, their service was unlike anything I have ever experience in a Mexican Mart before. Truly sad.</review>

<Gmap_id>0x808f856c4e13579d:0x9de485dab01d6eab<//Gmap_id><Name>Arno Hachaduryan</Name><Rate>5< /Rate>< Time>
1529947062335< /Time>
<response>None< /response>< pics>
[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOQn115D8RYOep4GiGSdJ9D-ANVAoYwv1SeArNR=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</pics>
< review>
I visited this range a week ago and I brought a friend with zero shooting experience and his brand new rifle. We'll get back to that.

The facilities are certainly sufficient. You won't encounter any specific shine or a feeling of "deluxe" here, but it is after all a shooting range that is also quite busy. They have an indoor range for handgun shooting (no Magnum ammo can be used there with the only exception being .22 caliber) that has automated target retrieval systems in place. They also have an outdoor pistol & rifle range. The pistol area outdoors has 12, 25 and 50 yard target distances while the rifle range has benches and the distance is set at 100 yards. The outdoor area operates on 15 minute shooting intervals followed by brief cease fire periods so the shooters can go inspect and replace targets as needed.

In my experience the staff was great! They were respectful but strict about safety rules (thanks for that, I wouldn't really feel safe otherwise) and they were also very helpful and cooperative. As I mentioned in the beginning my friend was a new shooter and had a brand new rifle that needed to be broken in properly, but neither him nor I knew much about how exactly to perform the process. One of the range officers took the time to guide us through it and help us where needed. I honestly did not expect such great service!

One thing worth mentioning is that if you get scolded by a range officer it isn't because they get off on that. During our visit there were a couple of patrons who heard the "safety speech" but that was only after they acted in an unsafe manner that was specifically listed as unacceptable in the rules of the facility. If you heard the speech don't be sore about it - you probably did something to deserve it.

A couple of recommendations:

1. Wear your ear protection as soon as your leave your car. It is quite loud, even in the parking lot.

2. Take their safety test if you want to get a 40% discount off your lane fee.

UPDATE: As of 2017 you CAN'T shoot .223 or 5.56 FMJ ammo at this range. Soft Point or Lead ammo are okay. I believe it has something to do with causing excessive damage to their back wall. Best call in advance if you have high powered, high velocity FMJ ammo.

Shotguns okay with slugs only.

Bottom line - I'll definitely be back there. It is conveniently placed close to where I live and I get to shoot outdoors, which is a definitely plus in my book.</review>

<GmapID>0x808f856c4e13579d:0x9de485dab01d6eab< /GmapID></record></dataset><record>
<Response>None< /Response><Time>1480100442817<//Time><rate>5<//rate><userid>113172575577148675531< /userid><user_name>Michael Chan<//user_name><GmapID>0x808f856c4e13579d:0x9de485dab01d6eab<//GmapID><Pictures>None< /Pictures><review>My first experience here was pretty good. Staff was very friendly, although the range master on the mic did have a sense of getting your attention over the loud speaker.

The basic layout is simple - indoor and outdoor range, the range master's office, a bathroom, and a parking lot. I have not been to the indoor range, but the outdoor range consists of handgun stalls and rifle stalls. You'll have to manually change your targets for the outdoor handgun stalls. The rifle stalls are set fairly far out (100 yards?).

It's fairly loud even in the parking lot, but you'll need ear protection at all times as you enter the property. Don't want tinnitus do ya?

There is a simple and free course safety test that'll get you discounted lane fees. Despite what other reviews have said, because of how pricing works, even without the test, the range fees are reasonably priced. Basically, you can shoot until you run out of ammo for a one-time fee. Coincidentally, you can buy more ammo at the range master's station.

Oh yeah, watch out for the spiders.<//review></record></dataset><record>

<Review>Staff is friendly and answers your questions. Available parking is light. I used the outdoor range, both short and long. They serve their purpose and that's about, it which is fine. They aren't clean or high end, it's just plywood marking you off from the shooter next to you. Because of their basic setup, the top of the wall doesn't close off with the ceiling/roof and lets things fall into your lane from above.

Here's the main problem; a hot casing from the lane next to me had fallen into my shirt and forced me to stop what I was doing to remove it and keep it from burning me. I was holding a loaded firearm which I had to knowingly keep pointed down range with my finger off the trigger all while scrambling to get this hot casing off of me. Luckily I was calm and aware of this, but this could have been easily someone else who could have caused a mishap and inured themselves or someone else. I hope that gets addressed.<//Review>< pictures>

<text>Wonderful first experience at this range.  I was welcomed as soon as I got there and treated well, and didn't see any hint of the attitude/sarcasm reported in other reviews.

The indoor range is well ventilated and doesn't have the constant linger of cordite that other nearby ranges have.  Maybe I just caught it on a good day, but the odor of the nearby waste treatment plant was hardly there.  It wasn't until I got outside afterwards and really tried that I could detect it.

I was given the discounted fee after taking the test on-the-spot, despite my physical safety card taking another week to process.  Anyone scoffing at the $25 lane fee: just take the test.  I don't think the point is to charge anyone $25, but rather give everyone incentive to sit down and think about safety for a bit.

No time limits on the line, plenty of stations, and best of all for me: they are open late enough most days that I can get in range time after work.  Lane fees are reasonably priced for the area.  Add in being a cool 15 minute drive away and having indoor and outdoor (rare in the area), and this became my go-to range from the first visit.</text><Resp>None<//Resp><user_id>108880945341691069152</user_id>< pics>

< user_name>
chris thejunglist< /user_name>
<UserId.>103907765613610679698</UserId.>< pictures>
None< /pictures>
< gmapID>
0x808f856c4e13579d:0x9de485dab01d6eab< /gmapID>
< text>
Local and not hard to get to, its a 5 minute drive from the 880 nestled at the west end of Davis St and if youre looking to get a few hours in after work, take a date, and/or just want to let off a few rounds its an ideal spot.Ill admit, there's some things that that inhibit me from giving it a 5 star but let me start out with the positive. They offer a indoor area, its well ventilated, well lit, and targets are a attached to motor operated draw string for easy adjustment of feet/yardage without interruption. The outside range however and understandably has 20 minute interruptions with a 10-15 minute (check, change, or remove target) period. The outside range offers up to 100 yard target practice with bench like seating. They also offer carpeted rest blocks for easy resting of your firearm (cleaning and target practice). The staff is friendly, always smiling, mainly older gents, and never had an issue but I cant see how you can have an issue if youre not familiar with firearm and/or range safety. Make no mistake, they will call you out, they got a PA system so everyone will hear it, and make it known if youre being unsafe in anyway. Most are knowledgeable in whatever your questions may be although most will leave you be if you know what youre doing.

Id like to add theres a nice little picnic area as well as a smoking area just a few feet from the firing line. Kind of a bonus if youre a smoker (i quit a few back) and I always bring a snack so its a plus for me in that regards.

They also have clean restrooms in case you need to take a break.

Now for the negative...First and foremost, you have to realize its location and location is the positive and negative in both situations, its a double edged sword.Its wedged right between the water treatment plant and the Davis street dumps so if youre sensitive to smell you'll notice it even before you pull into the parkinglot. Theres a minor pest problem (nats, flys, etc...)  and Im not gonna lie, its awful on a hot day, mix that with the smell of low tide from the bay and its almost unbearable, almost...

And lastly, my last gripe about the place is on the long range side (all the way over to the right) they only have (1) 50 yard target that pops down and if youre lucky enough to snag that seat your golden.

I recommend it to folks who live in the eastbay especially after chabots unfortunate announcement of their closure.

I want to clear the prices up and no I dont work and/or own the place. Its a 15 dollar flat fee with membership card with is free and all you have to do is take a firearm safety test which is also free and give you the basics on how they and most ranges operate. I read through the comments and most are incorrect not to mention you can tell a little butthurt about paying the 25 dollar no-membership fee so just do yourself a favor and get the membership if you plan on visiting more than once, you'll save money just on your second visit.

Needless to say, I wrote a lot here but its a honest review. I scrolled through most the reviews and its either bad or good but Ill be the first to tell you  Im quite thankful these guise (and girls) are still open to the public as most ranges are closed and/or closing due to environment issues with lead and what not. Just be humble we still have a place to go thats no more than 20 minutes in every direction to the locals here in the eastbay and again, thank you for providing a place we can all enjoy.

On a side note, Drakes brewery is located 5 minutes away, get place to grab a decent beer and a bite to eat after a good target practice!

Cheers,

~ Chris<//text>

Lots of picnic tables and play structures. Birds flitting through the trees. Small bridge crossing a small creek. Compact but charming.< /review>
</record></dataset><record>
< Review>
Not really what I expected.  Little cliffs for kids to fall off on the walking paths. Not crazy steep but someone could easily get hurt if they stepped wrong and tumbled down.  Super cool creaky old bridge that leads to a path, that leads right up to a road.  Play ground equipment says it's for smaller kids but all the slides are crazy high off the ground at the end. My kids were flying off right on to their bottoms pretty hard.  The ground is uneven,  the bathrooms were pretty bad,  cigarettes on the ground in the bathroom. No soap but they did have toilet paper. There were at least 6 homeless people hanging out but they didn't bother us and seemed friendly enough.  My kids had fun but I don't think we will be returning.< /Review>

< Review>
The greatest misconception and one I take offense to is hearing a personal injury attorney being called an "ambulance chaser". I suffered a horrible, life changing accident due to the negligence of another and if it weren't for Chris Dolan and the Dolan Law Firm, I'm not certain where I might be now. Chris treated me and my case, from the onset, like something that had happened to him personally and like a matter of life or death. He walked, talked, lived and breathed my case for nearly 4 years. His brilliance and extensive knowledge in both law as well as the medical field was a gross advantage to him winning a nearly 3 month jury trial against the City of San Francisco for me. Through it all, his focus remained clear and obvious. It was all me and what what would deliver the greatest outcome  for my situation. I've often heard others complain that lawyers get such a large % of an award but as far as I'm concerned, every penny & more is earned. Prior to this experience, I had no idea how much it takes to win a case or the tremendous expense and time which goes into it. All of which is absorbed on the front end by the attorney, with no guarantee of a positive outcome. Chris believes in justice and righting the wrongs. He was my voice when no one seemed to hear my words. He fearlessly and furiously stood up to an entity that could have easily mowed me over with trickery and outright lies. Chris had enough patience for the both of us when I would loose mine to keep going. I have never met another human being better at what he does than Chris Dolan is at protecting and fighting for his clients. He is one of the most brilliant attorneys of his time with a proven track record of his successful outcomes. He pours 100% into every case and selectively takes on many others shy away from. Never afraid of a challenge and always ready to take on even the largest corporate "bully", Chris Dolan and the Dolan Law Firm is better than the best! I would want nobody else in my corner if I ever find myself in a situation again needing a personal injury attorney.  Thank you Chris from the bottom of my heart!!! < Text>
I highly recommend the Dolan Law firm. Hands down, there is not a better personal injury attorney around. Chris Dolan is an expert in his field. He was truly amazing, honest, compassionate, professional, down to earth and very responsive. My accident involved being hit by a Yellow Cab while walking in a cross walk in San Francisco. Soon after my accident Chris and his assistant, Guillermo Bustillo came to our home to make sure I was doing ok. They spent more than 2 hours at my home taking down all necessary information and quickly agreed to represent me. Chris Dolan was extremely courteous, sympathetic and empathetic, and he was truly concerned for my well-being. The Dolan Law firm was professional and knowledgeable during the entire case process. He made sure all of my physical therapy costs and medical bills were covered, and I was never once harassed by the Defendants. The process was smooth and seamless. They took care of everything. The legal process was performed with perfection, care and expertise.  Deadlines were always met and I never worried how my case was being handled. My case took nearly two years, and as we were approaching the end and close to a settlement, a curve ball was thrown by Yellow Cab ‚Äì they filed for bankruptcy. Chris immediately called to reassure me that all of my out-of-pocket expenses would be handled and I did not need to worry. This would not be the end of my case. Given the drastic change of course in the settlement proceedings, he quickly developed a new plan of action which resulted in a fair compensation for me. The insurance company wanted to recoup all of their expenses. But, Chris Dolan and Guillermo Bustillo negotiated with the insurance company. They were able to successfully reduce the amount sought down to almost nothing! He further went above and beyond and personally called me to inform me he was reducing his firm fees.  Since no one could have expected Yellow Cab to file bankruptcy, Chris said he wanted to make sure I received as much compensation as possible. This case was not about ‚Äúmaking money‚Äù but instead about helping me. I highly recommend Chris Dolan to represent your legal matters. Chris Dolan‚Äôs drive, intellect and compassion set him apart from any other attorney I know. He truly cares about his clients and their best interests.</Text>

< rate>
2</rate>
< Text>
Fine ambience - In-efficient/super-novice hosts - awful Cocktails - OK-ish appetizers - Not at all impressive food (goat meat raw inside) - not going to recommend anyone to have your dinner here.
On a trip to San Diego from the bay area, me and my friends thought of hitting an Indian restaurant in the evening. We found that this restaurant had relatively higher rating the other ones in the area. So we decided to try Phulkari. The setup inside the restaurant looks nice. The host seemed novice from the beginning. Once my friends joined us after 15 minutes, we started ordering our food.
It is a busy weekend and we completely understand that it could be late to serve food and drinks. We started with cocktails. Each of them tasted pretty bad. Almost tasted like someone is trying out their hands for the first time. Even after getting one of the drinks fixed it tasted the same.
Later came the appetizers. It wasn't so great but tasted OK.
In the mean time the we are still waiting for the host to bring plates and silverware for one of our friends. Even after letting them know multiple times the food comes before and we had to keep on waiting for the plates.
The main food arrives in sometime. The food isn't served to appropriate person. It's just kept randomly on the table. We had to fix them on our own. Food Portions are less to be honest. We had ordered for a chicken, goat and a vegetable item. The rogan josh (goat) tasted like a regular goat curry with very strong taste of raw masala which is unusual in Indian food. Felt like not cooked properly. The meat was hard and the bigger chunks was raw/not-cooked inside. The chicken item tasted OK. The veg item was not impressive as well.

Over all with this disappointing experience here, I am never going to come back here any more neither will I recommend any body to try this one out.<//Text>

<Date>1472732744036</Date><rate>5<//rate><review>I had this pizza for the first time last night and I must say I'm impressed. The pizza has a great original taste with New York style inspiration. The restaraunt is family run with kind courteous people and speedy service.  The restaurant itself is slick and clean with upstairs and downstairs seating. The only criticism I have is the sign out front is a little plain and a product this memorable needs a more memorable logo.

{'time': 1522959756402, 'text': "Thank you for you feedback. Our pizzas are not New York style; it's Roman style. Our sauce is slow cooked for twelve hours and is low in acidity and sugar."}</Resp>
<user_id>117888646756321492548</user_id><pictures>None< /pictures>< text>
4 stars because it's fine for California pizza.  But I must say...if you're familiar with real NY-style pizza, and expecting anything close to that based on the other reviews...you're gonna have a bad time.

1)  They don't sell slices, they only sell personal pizzas.  You can't even find personal pizzas in New York...wanna know why?   A personal pizza is about 40% crust.  It just ruins the ratio.  Personal pizzas are for children who don't know any better.
2)  The crust is way too thin and crunchy.  New York style pizza crust is thin, but has some substance, and is soft enough to bend!  It's not supposed to be like eating a pizza-flavored cracker.
3)  The sauce is sweet and bland.  It lacks any hint of basil or herbs that good NY pizza has.  Also...they put the sauce on top of the cheese.  I don't even know what to say about that.

On the flip side, the cheese is very good though.  They make it fresh, and it shows.  They just need to fix everything else, and maybe it will be good "NY style" pizza.  Until then, for east-coasters at least, it's just another gimmicky and ultimately disappointing California pizza place.< /text>

<review>As someone with a lot of food sensitivities, it's fantastic to be able to talk to the owners, who great you very warmly, about the ingredients of thier mostly home made ingredients.
The buckwheat gluten free crust was delicious...Perfectly crunchy, something hard to accomplish with GF crusts.
Loved how the sauce was put on top, after the pizza was cooked.  The kids also loved thier pizzas, and easily ate them up.
Prices are standard SF pricey, but I don't see that as a problem when your able to actually enjoy the quality and understand what your eating.
We'll be back for sure, we love supporting local joints...<//review>< pictures>

<Text>Scott was helpful in assessing my needs since this was my first time getting a storage. Scott had me in and out faster than fast food while sharing with me my options in comparison. Definitely would recommend over the others; especially the cleanliness!< /Text>< Pics>
None<//Pics>

0x80dc749f9a31de93:0x567614eb22982eb9<//Gmap_id>

<user>117596634906891513760<//user>< name>
Caley Like<//name>
<Time>1563685534595</Time><rating>5<//rating>< text>
I can't say enough how terrific Scott and Richard is! I needed to get a small 5x5 storage unit that day. They are very understanding and listened to my situation.
We all know how google maps work when searching for a place. Though, don't let high reviews fool you, always visit them to see the location and talk with the staff in person.  Be kind and personable and you'll find out how they care about their work. Happy employees make for a happier business.  Anyhow.....

Upon researching online and visiting different Self Storage websites.... I've noticed there is a lot of online deals to be had right on their websites.  I narrowed it down to 4 different Self Storages. They all have very competitive prices online.  Though, one is way cheaper but does not compare to how well the other 3 maintain their properties.

Of the 4, I was able to narrow it down to just 2 Self Storages.  They both had great customer service, clean facilities, excellent security features and knew their business well.  Very close in rental prices online too.

Richard was helping me. Scott the manager, was helping another customer and I couldn't help but listen on the side. Great and awesome people!

Richard was able to answer all my questions and then some.  Security is top notch here.
- Gated with keypad
- Individually alarmed units
- Vented outside air into their facility. I couldn't find a climate controlled Self Storage around due to my time constraint and wanted to stay in carlsbad by Palomar Airport.
- They do use a special kind of lock that is set inside of the roll up doors with star keys. No hinges on their doors for padlocks. Another added security feature.  I don't mind.... I'll use StorQuest again in a heartbeat.
- Customer restroom. Well taken care of
- Surveillance system
- Free carts to use to move your goods
- Large Elevators
- Main building has a covered loading dock
- Well maintained
- Clean. Inside and out. Just a beautiful location
- Boxes and accessories if you need to buy.
- Go ask them about different leasing times.
- They do have different tiers on access times.  No 24 hour access.

- Though you have to buy storage rental insurance from them or provide your own.  An added cost, but I didn't mind for the price I was given.

Do check them out if you are looking! Check out their website first for availability and call if you have any questions about StorQuest. I feel very safe here and for my stuff.

I've added photos and a few videos of this place

P.S. All their doors are in the process of a color change.  Don't be alarmed if their outside doors are red and inside is blue. They are in the process changing it all to red.< /text>

I have been a customer for years and could have moved somewhere cheaper, but the people there make it worth the extra money.</Review>

< text>
Over the years (and in various locales), I‚Äôve had a number of storage units, and I can say without a doubt that my experience at StorQuest - Carlsbad / Campbell has been one of the best, if not the best, storage-unit experience I‚Äôve had.

First off, this place is CLEAN! Other places just don‚Äôt come close to the attractiveness and cleanliness of this place. And second, and high up on the list: both the manager, Scott Jedlick and his assistant, Richard offer great customer service. Prior to getting this storage unit, I checked out several places (over the phone and in person). During this period (person and phone), I talked to both Scott and Richard and they explained things well and came across as very professional, plus the rate I was quoted was extremely competitive. I got a 10‚Äô X 15‚Äô unit with StorQuest that was less expensive that some other places‚Äô 10‚Äô X 10‚Äô units.

I was a little hesitant about a second story unit, but Richard pointed out the dollies around the facility and with being able to park right next to the elevator (and with my unit being close to the elevator), I found that my initial fears were unwarranted. It was easy to access my unit, and to move things in and out of it.

At this place, they have you purchase a cylinder lock (~ $20.00 plus tax) to lock your unit. This is a very secure type of lock! In the past, at another storage facility, I had my lock cut open and my unit broken into. When I told this to StorQuest manager, Scott, he explained how secure and virtually-tamper proof these cylinder locks are.

There was one more thing that I really liked about this place: after punching in your code at the entrance, the buildings are arranged so that you drive (in one direction) in a big square and exit at the other side (where you again punch in your code for the exit gate to open). This seemed safer to me than cars and trucks coming and going in different directions, and like I said before, I was able to park right next to the elevator in my building. The driving space/path between the buildings was quite adequate so that cars and trucks could easily pass around cars parked to the side.

I had my unit at StorQuest for about 6 months until I could arrange to move my items out, and Scott was extremely helpful on my last day there (extending my gate access hours by two hours to accommodate my needs). If I ever need a storage unit again, and am in this North County area, I‚Äôd definitely use StorQuest - Carlsbad / Campbell again!</text>

<rate>5<//rate>< Text>
I recently was looking for a storage unit in the area. After reading some bad reviews of other places I stumbled across StorQuest. The reviews seemed legit so I decided to give it a look.

This was the first time I have ever rented a storage unit and most people don't get excited about storage units so I was skeptical.

I walked in and was greeted by Scott. First impression was fantastic. He was friendly and helpful. He walked me to through the whole process. Then he walked me to the unit I was about to rent. The hallways were clean, storage unit was in great shape, the indoor units are air conditioned, and they have security codes to protect your unit.

The following day I moved my stuff in. I pulled up to the gate and he came outside and greeted me with a smile. The move in went seem less (even though I was on the second floor). Moved right in and left without any issues.

VERY happy with StorQuest. If you are looking for a storage unit in the area I would highly recommend giving them a look. Chances are you will also be impressed.

Thanks Scott!</Text>

I recently signed a year long lease on a storage unit with StorQuest.  Ron was the manager I worked with and he was fantastic.  He was knowledgeable, kind and professional.  I had several concerns about storage facilities in general, as I had surveyed many of them in the area.  Most facilities allow transients to make storage units their residence.  When touring such facilities, I personally witnessed transients smoking crack and letting their pit bulls run loose on the premises.  But, Ron made clear that they didn't allow such conduct on their premises.  He explained the top notch security of this facility and that they don't allow riff raff to inhabit the premises, which was of particular importance to me since I'm storing highly confidential documents.  No joke, I surveyed probably 20 facilities in the Carlsbad/Oceanside area and this is by far and away the best one.  Thanks, Ron!< /review>

<Rating>5< /Rating>< Review>
This place is clean and well kept and it was unfair of me to give Scott a mediocre rating.  He does a good job and will go out on a limb for his tenants.  What I didn't know about StorQuest is they do automatic rate increases, like everybody else, in certain months of the year.  To avoid this rate increase, the tenant can opt to pay upfront for a long term lease (6 mos.) to lock in their rate.  I don't believe other storage facilities offer this.  Based upon this new information, I have revised my rating to a Five Star.  This is a nice facility where you're stuff is safe and protected.
It's too bad there aren't more storage facilities to provide competition hereby keeping the rates low. Us Baby Boomers like to hold onto our old stuff in case we need to sell it to make ends meet.<//Review>
<Pics>None< /Pics><resp>{'time': 1495732063353, 'text': 'Hi Geoffrey - Thanks for taking the time to provide your feedback. From time to time we must adjust rental rates to keep pace with the costs of maintaining a topnotch facility. We notify customers 30 days in advance to ensure they are aware of any changes taking place. However, we do offer long term discounts for customers who prepay six months to a year in advance, which locks in their rate for that period of time. We‚Äôd appreciate the opportunity to speak with you to gain a better understanding of your situation and encourage you to give us a call at your convenience 800-784-9176.'}<//resp>< Gmap_id>

<Rate>4< /Rate>< review>
This is my third time I have rented from StorQuest. Once in Temecula with a 10 x 25 and more recently upsizing from a 10 x 13 to a 10 x 25 in Carlsbad.
The staff at both locations was very helpful and friendly at all times!
There are two things that would have made my experience with using them a lot more remarkable:
1) a trash dumpster. Bite the bullet you guys! People will take advantage of this and it will cost you some, but the amount of $ your company makes monthly, every month for very little work to keep customers coming back?
2) the monthly rent on the 10 x 25 in Temecula $241 and the same size in Carlsbad $370??? WHY and no returning customer break?
I will endeavor to get rid of all my storage possessions soon as I cannot justify this expense at 66 years old!
